subject: Module 7 Problem Reference
content: Here's a fun one. Module 7 Problem Set 7 Problem 3 for some reason rounds a dollar amount to a single digit after the decimal point. Fine, I add a ROUND to round to a single digit. It turns out, though, in the expected answer, that the dollar amounts that had a 5 in the pennies spot (i.e. x.x5) were rounded down, not up. And it's not just concat to a single decimal point, since e.g. x.x8 is properly rounded up
